When editing an issue search, the status autocompletion drop-down menu gives incorrect visual feedback. As demonstrated by theattached screenshot, the drop-down menu offers an arbitrary subset of available status as possible completions, without giving a visual hint that this list is lacunary. This surprises the user and leads them into asking if the displayed statuses are special, how they can select the missing ones, etc.

I would expect a visual hint that the list is lacunary, and possibly a hint at how to find other possible completions.

(Interestingly, I was only able to attache the screenshot after I created the issue. Before this, I has a red error status like “JIRA could not attach the file as there was a missing token. Please try attaching the file again.”)

